1.1.0
=====
- Added ability to use the {ad} template function on the directory-link-details.tpl template (October 23, 2008)
- Fixed issue with keywords being rejected when there were exactly the number set as the limit (October 23, 2008)



1.1.0 BETA
==========
- Converted control panel interface Javascript library to jQuery
- Converted control panel interface to match style of TGPX and ToplistX
- More information is displayed for links in the control panel interface
- Updated error handling function to better process non-critical errors
- Default fonts included with the software for use with the verification code feature
- code.php script merged into a single file that can handle GD compiled with or without Freetype support
- Added option to use verification code on the "submit a bad link report" page
- Added ability to extract the site title, description, and keywords automatically from a page in the Add a Link interface
- Updated http.class.php scrip to work with PHP safe_mode enabled and using cURL
- Added ability to specify the value that will appear in mod_rewrite URLs for category links
- Added ability for the link scanner to extract the title, description, and keywords from sites for use in the directory
- Updated General Settings interface to automatically remove period included in the File Extension setting
- Added ability to include categories in the link import data instead of selecting a category to import links into
- Added simple ad rotation system for displaying advertisements in the link directory
- Added optimize/repair function in the Database Tools interface
- Added ability to track and display the search terms entered by end-users
- Fixed issue of new links not appearing on the directory index page when there were a large number of pending links
- Added category attribute to the {links} template function
- Added RSS feeds for the new, top rated, popular, and category directory pages
- Fixed error message when scanning links that forward (August 14, 2008)
- Fixed issue with date added value being set improperly for newly submitted links (August 14, 2008)
- Fixed issue with news items not displaying date values properly in the directory (August 19, 2008)
- Fixed issue with links not displaying date added values properly in the search results (August 29, 2008)


1.0.0 SNAPSHOT
==============
- Fixed error message when editing a link in the control panel interface (Dec 20, 2006)
- Fixed issue with account search interface links to display account links and comments not working (Dec 26, 2006)
- Fixed issue with category paths not properly updating when a category is edited (Dec 31, 2006)
- Updated the mod_rewrite file generation code to better handle all possible values for the details page setting (Dec 31, 2006)
- Fixed mod_rewrite issue when rating links and submitting comments (Jan 2, 2007)
- Added code to the global-header.tpl template to include the meta description and keywords on category pages (Jan 2, 2007)
- Fixed incorrect URL format issue when a user tries to rate a link more than once (Jan 6, 2007)
- Fixed issue with categories containing + characters causing problems with mod_rewrite (Jan 6, 2007)
- Fixed issue with access list warning message appearing after saving a template even if it is configured (Jan 30, 2007)
- Blank lines entered in the category name(s) field will now be skipped (Feb 20, 2007)
- Fixed email-link-confirm.tpl containing an invalid template value {$confirm_url} (March 12, 2007)
- Fixed issue with database backup function not working properly in IE (March 15, 2007)
- Updated directory-category.tpl template pagination code to point directly to the first page of a category instead of 1.html (March 28, 2007)
- Fixed issue with SQL error message when trying to re-submit a deleted unconfirmed account (May 18, 2007)
- Fixed issue with error message being generated when attempting to bulk blacklist links (May 21, 2007)
- Fixed error message generated on some versions of PHP when clearing the template cache (May 26, 2007)
- Fixed issue with error message when trying to restore database (June 21, 2007)
- Fixed issue with link scanner not correctly identifying sites that have a valid reciprocal link (October 15, 2007)
- Updated search to only include active links in the search results (November 12, 2007)
- Fixed issue with the initial site rating being incorrect when manually adding a link through the control panel (November 20, 2007)
- Fixed issue with sorting by Link ID in the browse interface (April 2, 2008)
- Error message will now display when an invalid link ID is supplied for the link details page (April 2, 2008)
- Fixed issue with IE7 not displaying the category selector properly when editing a link (April 2, 2008)
- Added error message when trying to add a category name that already exists (April 2, 2008)
- Updated the directory-category.tpl template so the first page of a category is never accessed using 1.html (April 2, 2008)
- Updated the {assign} template function so it will accept a value of zero (April 2, 2008)
- Added control panel error message that there must be at least one category before adding a link (April 2, 2008)
- Added link submission form error message that there must be at least one category before adding a link (April 2, 2008)
- Updated the directory-category.tpl template to display rating stars next to featured links (April 2, 2008)
- Fixed issues with updating user defined fields in both control panel and end-user interface (April 2, 2008)
- Fixed issue with {nocache} template function when the closing tag is on the same line (April 2, 2008)
- Added the reset-install.php utility script to completely reset an installation to it's default state (April 2, 2008)


1.0.0 - Dec 19, 2006
====================
- Directory templates updated so outgoing links open in a new window
- Added default value of 60 seconds for the command delay setting
- Updated database backup routine to properly handle user-defined fields
- User is now forwarded to the My Account page if they are already logged in and click on a login link
- Added the account-logout.tpl template which displays when a user chooses to logout of their account
- New accounts will use the default link weight, redirect, and reciprocal link requirement settings
- Updated link details URLs to be more search engine friendly
- All new default template set


1.0.0 BETA - Dec 6, 2006 12:14
==============================
- Added global-header.tpl and global-footer.tpl templates
- Added {include} template function for including global templates on other templates
- Added ability for users to logout of their account
- Added My Account tab in the directory templates so logged-in users can quickly access their account
- Category selection field on link submission form is now sorted by category path
- Fixed issue with category selector interface not displaying properly in IE7
- Fixed issue with link details not sliding up out of view properly in IE7
- Fixed issue with empty search type not returning correct results for comments and categories in control panel
- Updated prototype javascript library to latest version
- Updated scriptaculous javascript effects library to latest version
- Updated directory templates to support both mod_rewrite and standard linking
- Updated default template set to escape template values so there are fewer warnings when saving templates


1.0.0 BETA - Nov 20, 2006 14:55
===============================
- Added ability to browse to a category from the category search results page
- Fixed issue with link comment count not being properly updated when a comment was submitted
- Fixed issue with return URL containing an ? instead of & after rating a link
- Fixed issue with return URL containing an ? instead of & after submitting a comment
- Updated link import function to better handle improperly formatted expiration dates
- Fixed issue with link status being overwritten by the link type during link import if an invalid type was provided
- Fixed issue of trying to view the link a comment is for not displaying any search results
- Added editor account privilege check when editing a user submitted comment
- Added check to prevent a category with sub-categories or links from being changed to a crosslink category
- Added check to prevent a crosslink category from pointing to itself
- Several updates to the date/time functions to handle server moves and timezone changes seamlessly


1.0.0 BETA - Nov 14, 2006 10:01
===============================
- Updated user account search interface to automatically show details for pending accounts
- Updated comment search interface to automatically show details for pending comments
- Updated the access list feature to accept hostnames and partial hostnames in the list
- Fixed issue with not being able to approve/reject single comments at a time using the function icons
- Replaced phpmailer.class.php third party library with internally developed e-mail library
- Link scanner function is now completed


1.0.0 BETA - Nov 6, 2006 15:37
==============================
- Fixed compatibility issues with PHP versions 5 and newer
- Added ability to run the phpinfo() function from the control panel
- Majority of the software documentation is now complete


1.0.0 BETA - Nov 4, 2006 12:53
==============================
- Removed blank lines from the end of json.class.php that caused some versions of PHP to generate an error message
- Fixed issue with search results page showing an illegal division by zero error message
- Fixed MySQL error message when editing a link and there are no user defined fields defined
- Fixed MySQL error message when editing an account and there are no user defined fields defined
- Added link to details page on the new links and popular links directory templates


1.0.0 BETA - Nov 3, 2006
========================
- Initial public release of LinkX